## Layout

Layers, imports point DOWN only (`core` < `{{ package_name }}`{% if has_viewer %} < `{{ viewer_name }}`{% endif %}):

- `core/` — the clean kernel: pure, shared, imports nothing above it.
- `{{ package_name }}/` — the trainer/orchestration layer, built on `core`.
{% if has_viewer %}- `{{ viewer_name }}/` — the viewer/edge consumer of `core`{% if viewer_imports_trainer %} (may also reuse `{{ package_name }}`){% endif %}.
{% endif %}- `tests/` — `unit/`, `integration/`, `e2e/`.
- `devtools/` — the arch-fitness engine (`graph.py`).

## Quickstart

```bash
uv sync --extra dev --extra devtools
nox -s lint test cov
```

## Gates

`nox -s lint test cov` (or `nox -s gates`) runs exactly what CI runs:

- **lint** — ruff check (pinned) + ruff format --check (advisory) + vulture + import-linter{% if enforce_arch_fitness %} + arch-fitness (`graph.py --assert`){% endif %}.
- **test** — pytest.
- **cov** — pytest --cov with a `--fail-under={{ coverage_floor }}` floor.
